## TEST CASE 1: STEMI

After implementation, test with this input:

```
65 saal ke diabetic patient, chest pain aur breathlessness se aaye hain. 
ECG mein ST elevation hai anterior leads mein. Troponin I positive - 2.5 ng/ml. 
BP 90/60, pulse 110, SpO2 92% on room air. 
Patient ko ICU admission chahiye, primary PCI ke liye cardiology referral. 
Star Health policy hai, sum insured 10 lakh.
```

**Expected PDF Output:**

| Field | Expected Value |
|-------|----------------|
| Patient Age | 65 years |
| Insurer | Star Health |
| Sum Insured | ₹10,00,000 |
| Diagnosis | Acute myocardial infarction / STEMI |
| ICD-10 | I21.3 or I21.9 |
| Room Category | ICU |
| ICU Days | 3+ |
| Severity | Critical |
| Cost | ₹2.5-5 lakh |
| Comorbidities | Diabetes |

**If ANY of these fail, check the Debug Panel to see WHERE the data got lost.**

---

## WHY THIS ARCHITECTURE WORKS

1. **Single Source of Truth**: All data lives in `InsuranceCase`. No parallel state. No caching.

2. **Source Tracking**: Every field knows WHERE it came from (voice, manual, computed). You can trace any bug.

3. **Validation Gates**: PDF cannot be generated if data is invalid. No more "R69" or "2005 years" in production.

4. **Event-Driven Pipeline**: Voice → Parser → State → Engines → Validation → PDF. Clear flow.

5. **Debug Panel**: Real-time visibility into state. You can SEE when data is missing or wrong.

6. **Immutable Updates**: State changes through dispatch, not direct mutation. Predictable.

This is production-grade architecture. It will work reliably because the failure modes are eliminated by design.